body:
https://github.com/verilator/verilator/pull/7108 caused some reductions to not compile. 

Minimal reproduction case:

~~~ systemverilog
class uvm_object;
endclass

class riscv_instr_gen_config extends uvm_object;
  rand int sub_program_instr_cnt[];
  constraint debug_mode_c {
    sub_program_instr_cnt.sum() == 200;
  }
endclass

module top;
  riscv_instr_gen_config gen_config;
  initial begin
    gen_config = new;
    void'(gen_config.randomize());
  end
endmodule
~~~

Before it verilated with `CONSTRAINTIGN` warning and now it fails with following error:

~~~
%Error: Internal Error: bugpoint.sv:7:30: ../V3Scope.cpp:88: Can't locate varref scope
                                        : ... note: In instance '$unit.riscv_instr_gen_config'
    7 |        sub_program_instr_cnt.sum() == 200;
      |                              ^~~
~~~



The problem doesn't occur when `riscv_instr_gen_config` doesn't extend a class.
